gomodel:SYNGO_2027  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Shaky mice have spontaneous mutation of the GLRA1 coding sequence. The Shaky GLRA1 has defective trafficking to postsynapses and displays problems with glycinergic (blocked by strychnine in WT animals) postsynaptic responses in PreBötC neurons.. Experimental description: \"Shaky mice have impaired glycinergic synaptic transmission in PreBötC neurons. \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
